    "summary": "Experienced Professor with a demonstrated background in genomics & musculoskeletal health research. Skilled in (Genetic) Epidemiology, Life Sciences, Medicine, Endocrinology and Clinical Research. The core of my research focuses on the identification of genetic determinants of musculoskeletal traits applying high throughput technology, (i.e., GWAS and NGS). My work focusing on \"Musculoskeletal Health and Translational Genomics\" is done primarily applying a life-course epidemiological approach within the Generation R (a multi-ethnic birth cohort in Rotterdam) and the Rotterdam Study (a large population-based study of disease and disability in the elderly) cohorts, in the collaborative setting of large international consortia.",
